AFRICAN HORSE SICKNESS - SOUTH AFRICA (WESTERN CAPE) (03)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: Wed 15 Nov 2006
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: SABC News - Auckland Park, South Africa [edited]
<http://www.sabcnews.com/south_africa/health/0,2172,138503,00.html>

There is a suspected outbreak of the highly infectious African horse
sickness in the Southern Cape. One horse in Knysna is suspected to have
contracted the disease.
Cobus Dowry, the Western Cape minister of agriculture, says the results of
tests will be known later today [15 Nov 2006]. Dowry says if the horse has
the deadly sickness, it would be a blow to the export trade. He says the
department lost R 120 million [USD 16 563 190] 2 years ago, when a ban was
introduced on the export of horses.
"There was one suspected case in the Knysna area that was referred by a
private veterinary surgeon to the Onderstepoort laboratories to check out
whether there is horse sickness in that area. If there is ... we will have
a problem. But we hope that this was a small case and there's nothing to
worry about," Dowry said.
--
